# I2C clock-stretching simulator: count stretched cycles.
*i2c_stretch(stretch_flags as Vec of i64, n as i64, max_per as i64) returns i64
    total is 0
    i is 0
    while i < n
        c is 0
        while stretch_flags.get(i) equals 1 and c < max_per
            c is c + 1
        total is total + c
        i is i + 1
    total

*main
    f is vec()
    f.push(0)
    f.push(1)
    f.push(0)
    f.push(1)
    f.push(1)
    log i2c_stretch(f, 5, 4)
